</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-32_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-33_ pf-text-1"><strong>Automated External Defibrillator (AED)</strong> - A portable device that analyses the heart's rhythm and delivers an electric shock if necessary to restore normal rhythm.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Cardiac arrest </strong>- The abrupt loss of heart function, typically caused by an electrical malfunction in the heart, leading to an irregular heartbeat (arrhythmia).






























































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-37_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">Legislation, regulations, and best practice</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-41_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-42_ pf-text-1">The Health and Safety (First Aid) Regulations 1981 (as amended) mandate employers to provide adequate first aid equipment, which may include AEDs, based on their risk assessment.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-44_ pf-text-1">Resuscitation Council UK provides guidelines on AED placement, maintenance, and staff training to optimise response to cardiac emergencies.































































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-46_ pf-text-1">British Heart Foundation (BHF) advocates for widespread AED deployment in public spaces and emphasises public education on AED use through initiatives like "Call Push Rescue."































































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-48_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-49_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-50_ pf-heading-1-h3">Understanding AED functionality</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-52_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>AEDs are user-friendly devices with voice prompts and visual cues to guide responders through resuscitation. They analyse the heart's rhythm and, if necessary, prompt the user to deliver a shock to restore normal rhythm. Modern AEDs are designed for simplicity, enabling even untrained individuals to operate them effectively in critical situations.











 

  
<br>
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-54_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-55_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-56_ pf-heading-1-h3">AED placement and accessibility</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-58_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Strategic placement of AEDs is crucial for maximising their impact. High-traffic public areas, workplaces, and community spaces should prioritise AED installation, ensuring rapid access during emergencies. Regular maintenance and monitoring are essential to guarantee device readiness.












 

  
<br>
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-60_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-61_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-62_ pf-heading-1-h3">Training and preparedness</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-64_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Training in AED operation and cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) empowers individuals to respond confidently during cardiac emergencies. Employers and community organisations should invest in comprehensive training programs to equip staff and volunteers with life-saving skills.













 

  
<br>
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-66_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-67_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-68_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
